Metadata-Version: 1.0
Name: S3ImageResize
Version: 0.1.6
Summary: Script to resize images on S3.
Home-page: https://github.com/dirkcuys/s3imageresize
Author: Dirk Uys
Author-email: dirk@p2pu.org
License: LICENSE.txt
Description: Resize images hosted on Amazon S3 using Pillow
        
        ## Installation
        
            pip install s3imageresize
        
        ## Usage
        
        Make sure your `AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID` and `AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY` are exported as environmental variables
        
        In code:
        
            from s3imageresize import resize_image_folder
            resize_image_folder(bucket_name, prefix, (width, height))
        
        From the command line:
        
            s3resizeimagefolder.py bucketname prefix width height
        
Platform: UNKNOWN
